<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="595" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Local distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="595">
The species was described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Chorthippus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chorthippus kozhevnikovi subsp. arenosus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="kozhevnikovi" subSpecies="arenosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Chorthippus kozhevnikovi arenosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bey-Bienko from the vicinities of Aul settlement, Semipalatinskij District (now in the East Kazakhstan Province, Kazakhstan) (Bey-Bienko, 1930b). The rare populations of this species occured (and occur) only in the dry sandy steppe habitats (often together with 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. antennatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" rank="species" species="antennatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">M. antennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In 2004-2006 the average density of one population varied between 0.16 and 1.32/m2 (dry sandy steppe, near Rakity settlement, Kulunda steppe).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
